intro: Dimorphanthera denticulifera var. denticulifera, commonly known as the toothed-leaf dimorphanthera, is a flowering plant native to Southeast Asia. It is characterized by its distinctive, serrated leaves and clusters of small, fragrant flowers. The plant typically grows in moist, shaded environments such as forest undergrowth.
